## Particle spawning

There is a separate array:

```js
let streams = [];
let tick = 0;
```

A function periodically creates particles from random nodes.

```js
function spawnStreamParticle() {
  if (streams.length >= config.streamMax) return;

  const node = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  const angle = Math.random() * TAU;
  const speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * ROOT_HALF;

  streams.push({
    x: node.x,
    y: node.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
    size: 0.8 + (Math.random() * PHI) * ROOT_HALF
  });
}
```

So particles:
- start at a random node
- move in a random direction
- have finite lifetime
- get a random size

---

## Particle update

```js
function updateStreams() {
  for (let i = streams.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    const p = streams[i];

    p.age++;
    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;

    p.vx *= 1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125;
    p.vy *= 1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125;

    if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
      streams.splice(i, 1);
    }
  }
}
```

Particles just drift and slowly slow down, then disappear.

